once the owner feels that he is making a sufficient profit from you, he will often give you additional goods at a rate close to his cost, rather than the common "foreigner rate". you will get better prices and service by buying many items in one store than by bargaining in multiple stores individually. if you see local people buying in a store, you can probably get the real indian prices. ask someone around you quietly, "how much would you pay for this?" also, very often you will meet a "friend" in the street inviting you to visit their family's 